null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2017-12-22T07:19:08Z", "updated_at": "2020-05-30T15:28:49Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "#### What is the problem?\r\n\r\nIn `consts.py` we define stuff like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nDATALAD_GIT_DIR = join('.git', 'datalad')\r\nANNEX_TEMP_DIR = join('.git', 'annex', 'tmp')\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think this is inappropriate, because `.git` can easily be a file. That is why we have `get_git_dir(path)` that will report the actual location of `.git/`, possibly by reading it from a .git file. Such constants should probably just identify the name inside the `.git/` directory.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/2054/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/2054/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}